========================================
Required tools
========================================

- 7Zip: http://www.7-zip.org/download.html
- SUN Java SDK 1.6: http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
- Eclipse 3.4+: http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
- Apache Ant 1.7: http://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi
- MSysGit 1.6: http://code.google.com/p/msysgit/

========================================
Initial development environment setup
========================================

** Note: all names between < and > are meant to be replaced by the corresponding information.

1. Install 7Zip, Java SDK, Eclipse, Ant, and MSysGit
2. Use GitHub Web page to fork Twetailer master repository (then you'll have you own copy into your account)
3. Open a command line shell
	3.1 Go to your Eclipse workspace directory: $cd <workspace.dir>
	3.2 Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
	3.3 Clone your fork of Twetailer repository: $git clone git@github.com:<your.username>/twetailerJ
	3.4 Keep a local reference of the master respository: $git remote add domderrien git://github.com/domderrien/twetailerJ
	3.5 Move to the twetailerJ sub-directory: $cd twetailerJ
	3.6 Unzip the Google App Engine SDK: $<7Zip.dir>\7z.exe x -obin deps\tools\containers\appengine-java-sdk-<last.version>.zip
	3.7 Move to the build sub-directory: $cd build
	3.8 Run the Ant command: $<ant.dir>\bin\ant.bat -f build\build-appengine.xml init
	
========================================
Day-to-day development
========================================

1. Open Eclipse to update your files
2. Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
3. Move to the twetailerJ\build directory: $cd <workspace.dir>\twetailerJ\build
4. Run the tests with the Ant command: $<ant.dir>\bin\ant.bat -f build\build-appengine.xml test
5. Run the App Engine server with the Ant command: $<ant.dir>\bin\ant.bat -f build\build-appengine.xml webserver-start
6. Note that server can only be kill with the Task Manager... This might be fixed within a future release of the App Engine SDK

========================================
Submit your updates
========================================

1. Run the Ant command: $<ant.dir>\bin\ant.bat -f build\build-appengine.xml clean
2. Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
3. Move to the twetailerJ directory: $cd <workspace.dir>\twetailerJ
3. Use Git to submit your patch:
		$git status
		$git add <new.file.path>
		$git commit -a -m "<informative.message.about.the.patch>"
		$git push
4. Or ZIP the Twetailer files and send them to dom.derrien@twetailer.com:
		$<7Zip.dir>\7z.exe a -xr!.git -ptwtlr<YYYYMMDD.of.the.day> twetailerJ-patch-<YYYYMMDD.of.the.day>.7z ./*